name: Roger A. PRATT v. Marion I. PRATT

parties: Roger A. PRATT v. Marion I. PRATT.

opinions.text:
ORDER
This case came before us on a motion to show cause why the husband’s appeal should not be denied and dismissed.
Cause having been shown, this case will be assigned to the regular calendar for February, 1981.

attorneys: Paul P. Baillargeon, Paul P. Baillargeon, Inc., Woonsocket, for petitioner.
Dianne Curran, Rhode Island Legal Services, Inc., Providence, for respondent.
casebody.head_matter:
Roger A. PRATT v. Marion I. PRATT.
No. 80-509-Appeal.
Supreme Court of Rhode Island.
Dec. 11, 1980.
Paul P. Baillargeon, Paul P. Baillargeon, Inc., Woonsocket, for petitioner.
Dianne Curran, Rhode Island Legal Services, Inc., Providence, for respondent.
